Sea%2C%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20Turkey%20February%2013%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FYoruk%20Isik%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EUkraine's%20attack%20on%20the%20Sevastopol%20shipyard%20last%20week%20left%20a%20Russian%20submarine%20in%20rough%20shape.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBritain's%20defense%20ministry%20said%20recently%20that%20the%20vessel%20%26quot%3Blikely%20suffered%20catastrophic%20damage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ENew%20photos%20leaked%20to%20social%20media%20indicate%20the%20submarine%20may%20be%20beyond%20repair%2C%20a%20naval%20expert%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20photos%20of%20what%20is%20said%20to%20be%20a%20Russian%20submarine%20targeted%20in%20a%20Ukrainian%20missile%20attack%20show%20severe%20and%20widespread%20damage%20to%20its%20exterior%2C%20and%20possibly%20interior.%20A%20naval%20expert%20and%20former%20submariner%20says%20the%20damage%20may%20leave%20the%20vessel%20beyond%20repair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20forces%20last%20week%20carried%20out%20a%20series%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhuge-crimea-attack-ukraine-pry-black-sea-base-russia-navy-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecruise%20missile%20strikes%20on%20a%20shipyard%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%20port%20city%20of%20Sevastopol%2C%20which%20is%20located%20on%20the%20southwestern%20edge%20of%20occupied%20Crimea%20and%20is%20the%20headquarters%20for%20Russia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%20(BSF).%20The%20attack%20damaged%20two%20vessels%2C%20including%20the%20Kilo-class%20attack%20submarine%20Rostov-on-Don%2C%20and%20was%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-missile-attack-naval-base-helps-make-crimea-untenable-russia-2023-9%5C%22%3Estring%20of%20assaults%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20peninsula%2C%20which%20Kyiv%20has%20vowed%20to%20liberate%20from%20Moscow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESatellite%20imagery%20obtained%20by%20Insider%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20attack%20showed%20clear%20damage%20to%20the%20shipyard%20and%20the%20two%20vessels%2C%20although%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20destruction%20was%20not%20immediately%20clear.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20new%20photographs%20said%20to%20be%20of%20the%20submarine%2C%20which%20circulated%20around%20social%20media%20on%20Monday%2C%20appear%20to%20show%20the%20attack%20sub%20in%20rough%20shape.%20The%20images%2C%20which%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20independently%20verify%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCITeam_en%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobtained%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Conflict%20Intelligence%20Team%2C%20an%20open-source%20intelligence%20operation%2C%20and%20shared%20by%20other%20OSINT%20platforms%2C%20like%20Oryx%2C%20which%20maintains%20a%20database%20of%20both%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20equipment%20and%20weapons%20losses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Oryx%20(%40oryxspioenkop)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1703728356208881975%5C%22%3ESeptember%2018%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20Clark%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Navy%20submarine%20officer%20and%20defense%20expert%20at%20the%20Hudson%20Institute%2C%20said%20the%20purported%20damage%20looks%20%26quot%3Bbad%20enough%20to%20make%20the%20submarine%20a%20total%20loss.%26quot%3B%20According%20to%20Oryx's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oryxspioenkop.com%2F2022%2F02%2Fattack-on-europe-documenting-equipment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20keeps%20a%20tally%20of%20Russian%20ships%20taken%20out%20by%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Rostov-on-Don%20is%20recorded%20as%20Moscow's%20first%20submarine%20loss%20in%20the%20ongoing%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20hole%20at%20the%20side%20on%20the%20waterline%20is%20accurately%20depicted%2C%20the%20flooding%20that%20would%20have%20resulted%20should%20have%20made%20saving%20the%20ship%20very%20difficult%20and%20likely%20damaged%20much%20of%20equipment%20inside%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%20%26quot%3BIt%20also%20looks%20like%20the%20explosion%20pushed%20the%20hull%20out%20rather%20than%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20could%20be%20the%20result%20of%20a%20sympathetic%20explosion%20inside%20the%20ship%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bsuggesting%20extensive%20damage%20inside%20the%20hull.%20There%20is%20also%20some%20less%20significant%20damage%20on%20the%20superstructure%2C%20which%20would%20be%20repairable%20if%20the%20ship%20could%20be%20saved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark's%20analysis%20follows%20a%20similar%20assessment%20from%20Britain's%20defense%20ministry%2C%20which%20wrote%20in%20a%20Friday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefenceHQ%2Fstatus%2F1702561936179630440%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eintelligence%20update%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20submarine%20%26quot%3Blikely%20suffered%20catastrophic%20damage%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20any%20effort%20to%20eventually%20return%20the%20vessel%20to%20service%20could%20take%20years%20and%20cost%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20loss%20of%20the%20Rostov%20removes%20one%20of%20the%20BSF's%20four%20cruise-missile%20capable%20submarines%20which%20have%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20striking%20Ukraine%20and%20projecting%20Russian%20power%20across%20the%20Black%20Sea%20and%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%2C%26quot%3B%20Britain's%20defense%20ministry%20said.%20It%20also%20published%20satellite%20imagery%20showing%20the%20damaged%20Sevastopol%20shipyard%2C%20with%20a%20zoomed-in%20view%20of%20the%20submarine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221168%5C%22%20