.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25123828%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_03.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20petitioner%20in%20the%20Adani-Hindenburg%20case%20has%20urged%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20make%20a%20new%20expert%20committee%2C%20alleging%20conflict%20of%20interest%20by%20the%20current%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20March%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20constituted%20the%20committee%20headed%20by%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20Justice%20A.%20M.%20Sapre%2C%20to%20look%20into%20whether%20a%20regulatory%20failure%20had%20led%20to%20investors%20losing%20money%20after%20the%20short%20seller%20Hindenburg%20Research%E2%80%99s%20report%20pointed%20to%20fraud%20and%20manipulation%20by%20the%20Adani%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20has%20former%20bankers%20K.V.%20Kamath%20and%20O.P.%20Bhatt%2C%20Infosys%20cofounder%20Nandan%20Nilekani%2C%20securities%20lawyer%20Somasekhar%20Sundaresan%20and%20retired%20high%20court%20judge%20J.P.%20Devadhar.%20This%20committee%20was%20formed%20after%20the%20apex%20court%20rejected%20the%20names%20suggested%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20as%20members%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20and%20announced%20the%20formation%20of%20its%20won%20expert%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20six-member%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadani-hindenburg-allegations-sc-appointed-panel-submits-report-in-a-sealed-cover%5C%22%3Ehad%20submitted%20its%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20to%20the%20apex%20court%20on%20May%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20has%20filed%20an%20application%20saying%20that%20many%20in%20the%20panel%20may%20have%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20submitted%20that%20Mr%20O.P.%20Bhatt%2C%20one%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Expert%20Committee%2C%20and%20the%20former%20chairman%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20is%3Cbr%3E%20presently%20working%20as%20the%20Chairman%20of%20Greenko%2C%20a%20leading%20renewable%20energy%20company.%20Since%20March%2C%202022%20Greenko%20and%20Adani%20Group%20are%20working%20in%20a%20close%20partnership%20to%20provide%20energy%20to%20Adani%20Groups%20facilities%20in%20India.%20Greenko%20issued%20a%20press%20release%20dated%2014.03.2022%20regarding%20their%20partnership%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petition%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20the%20petition%20alleges%20that%20Bhatt%20was%20examined%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20March%202018%20in%20a%20case%20of%20alleged%20wrongdoing%20in%20disbursing%20loans%20to%20the%20former%20liquor%20baron%20and%20fugitive%20economic%20offender%2C%20Vijay%20Mallya%20who%20is%20accused%20of%20defrauding%20banks%2C%20including%20SBI%2C%20of%20US%20%241.2%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBhatt%20served%20as%20the%20SBI%20chairman%20between%202006%20and%202011%20when%20the%20majority%20of%20these%20loans%20were%20advanced%20to%20Mallya%E2%80%99s%20companies.%20CBI%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20SBI-led%20consortium%20of%20lenders%20did%20not%20conduct%20any%20%E2%80%98forensic%20audit%E2%80%99%20despite%20being%20aware%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98poor%20financial%20health%E2%80%99%20of%20Mallya%E2%80%99s%20companies%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20application%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20has%20also%20submitted%20that%20another%20member%20of%20the%20expert%20committee%2C%20K.V.%20Kamath%2C%20who%20was%20the%20chairman%20of%20ICICI%20Bank%20from%201996%20to%202009%2C%20figured%20in%20a%20CBI%20FIR%20in%20the%20ICICI%20Bank%20fraud%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20case%20relates%20to%20Ms.%20Chanda%20Kocchar%20who%20served%20as%20the%20Managing%20Director%20and%20CEO%20of%20ICICI%20Bank%20from%202009%20to%202018.%20The%20CBI%20alleged%20that%20she%20and%20her%20family%20received%20various%20kickbacks%20over%20her%20tenure%20in%20lieu%20of%20loans%20provided%20to%20the%20Videocon%20group%2C%20many%20of%20which%20turned%20into%20non-%20performing%20assets%20(NPAs).%20Kamath%20was%20the%20non-executive%20chairman%20of%20the%20bank%20when%20some%20of%20those%20loans%20were%20approved%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20committee%20that%20sanctioned%2Fapproved%20the%20loans%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20petitioner%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20has%20also%20repeated%20that%C2%A0Somashekhar%20Sundaresan%20has%20been%20a%20lawyer%20representing%20Adani%20before%20various%20forums%20including%20the%20SEBI%20Board.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20field%20experts%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfield%20of%20finance%2C%20law%20and%20stock%20market%20with%20impeccable%20integrity%2C%20and%20who%20have%20no%20conflict%20of%20interest%20in%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20instant%20matter%E2%80%9D%20and%20reconstitute%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695069005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25123828%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_03.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadani-hindenburg-supreme-court-conflict-of-interest-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20petitioner%20has%20filed%20an%20application%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asking%20for%20the%20committee%20to%20be%20reconstituted.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadani-hindenburg-supreme-court-conflict-of-interest-panel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adani-Hindenburg%20Case%20Petitioner%20Alleges%20Conflict%20of%20Interest%20of%20SC-Appointed%20Expert%20Panel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20petitioner%20in%20the%20Adani-Hindenburg%20case%20has%20urged%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20make%20a%20new%20expert%20committee%2C%20alleging%20conflict%20of%20interest%20by%20the%20current%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E