%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fsherri-shepherd-talk-show-return-amid-strikes-union-1235726468%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fsherri-shepherd-talk-show-return-amid-strikes-union-1235726468%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Twenty%20Seven%20Years%20in%20the%20Making%2C%20a%20Guide%20to%20the%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill's%20Tortuous%20History%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F09%2Fwomens-reservation-bill-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20first%20published%20on%20September%2016%2C%202016%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20reports%20the%20Union%20cabinet%20has%20cleared%20its%20introduction%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20At%20any%20given%20point%20of%20time%2C%20several%20draft%20legislations%20listed%20under%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98pending%20bills%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20exist.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20however%2C%20has%20been%20pending%20since%202010%20given%20the%20patriarchal%20tendencies%20of%20most%20political%20parties%20that%20share%20power%20in%20the%20country%20and%20the%20indifference%20of%20successive%20governments%20towards%20the%20political%20empowerment%20of%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20on%20September%2012%2C%20the%20108th%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%20or%20what%20is%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%20completed%2027%20years%20of%20being%20in%20existence%20%E2%80%93%20while%20managing%20to%20get%20only%20the%20assent%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20thus%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20the%20Bill%20has%20seen%20much%20drama%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament%2C%20clearly%20aimed%20at%20scuttling%20the%20measure%2C%20with%20some%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fnewswire%2Fstory%2Fvoting-on-womens-bill-deferred-unruly-scenes-in-rs%2F676149%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emembers%20even%20attempting%20to%20physically%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20then%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Hamid%20Ansari%2C%20to%20disrupt%20its%20tabling.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%E2%80%99s%20journey%20began%20on%20September%2012%2C%201996%2C%20when%20it%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20the%20United%20Front%20government%20of%20H.D.%20Deve%20Gowda.%20The%20bill%20called%20for%20reserving%2033%25%20of%20the%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20all%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20for%20women.%20As%20per%20the%20draft%2C%20the%20seats%20were%20to%20be%20reserved%20for%20women%20on%20a%20rotation%20basis%20and%20would%20be%20determined%20by%20draw%20of%20lots%2C%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20a%20seat%20would%20be%20reserved%20only%20once%20in%20three%20consecutive%20general%20elections.%20It%20said%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%20would%20cease%20to%20exist%2015%20years%20after%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20amendment%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20however%2C%20failed%20to%20get%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20house%20then%20and%20was%20instead%20referred%20to%20a%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee.%20The%20committee%20submitted%20its%20report%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20two%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201998%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%20who%20headed%20the%20the%20first%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20government%2C%20reintroduced%20the%20Bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20After%20Vajpayee%E2%80%99s%20law%20minister%2C%20M.%20Thambidurai%20introduced%20it%20in%20the%20house%2C%20a%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20MP%20snatched%20it%20from%20the%20speaker%20and%20tore%20it%20into%20bits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20Bill%20lapsed%20and%20was%20reintroduced%20%E2%80%93%20in%201999%2C%20in%202002%20and%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.knightlab.com%2Flibs%2Ftimeline3%2Flatest%2Fembed%2Findex.html%3Fsource%3D1601B6of0DDLcqevG_UcSmg9POp-SSf0RVP-fHv36Cyk%26font%3DDefault%26lang%3Den%26initial_zoom%3D2%26height%3D650%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20parliamentary%20impasse%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20Left%20and%20the%20BJP%20were%20heard%20openly%20pledging%20support%20for%20the%20Bill%2C%20it%20just%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20passed%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20In%201998%2C%20the%20Vajpayee%20government%20was%20certainly%20dependent%20on%20other%20parties%20for%20survival%20which%20many%20political%20observers%20often%20suggest%20was%20a%20reason%20for%20not%20being%20able%20to%20%E2%80%9Cassert%E2%80%9D%20itself.%20After%20the%201999%20mid-term%20polls%2C%20even%20though%20Vajpayee%20returned%20to%20the%20saddle%2C%20the%20mandate%20was%20for%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20which%20won%20303%20of%20the%20544%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20yet%20again%20a%20situation%20where%20he%20%E2%80%9Chad%20to%20keep%E2%80%9D%20all%20the%20parties%20together.%20However%2C%20given%20the%20support%20pledged%20by%20the%20Congress%20and%20Left%2C%20the%20Bill%20would%20have%20sailed%20through%20the%20house%20had%20it%20been%20formally%20put%20to%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh%20government%20introduced%20the%20bill%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20Two%20years%20later%20on%20March%209%2C%202010%2C%20a%20huge%20political%20barrier%20was%20overcome%20when%20it%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20house%20in%20spite%20of%20high%20drama%20and%20scuffles%20between%20members.%20The%20BJP%2C%20the%20Left%20and%20some%20other%20parties%20came%20together%20with%20the%20ruling%20Congress%20to%20help%20pass%20it%20in%20the%20upper%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20have%20passed%20since%20that%20moment%20when%20top%20women%20leaders%20from%20three%20major%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20and%20Brinda%20Karat%20%E2%80%93%20gave%20a%20rare%20moment%20to%20media%20photographers%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fopinion%2Farticle256086.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalking%20hand%20in%20hand%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20impromptu%20celebration%20of%20that%20%E2%80%98historic%20occasion%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20in%202016%2C%20it%20has%20still%20not%20seen%20the%20light%20of%20the%20day%2C%20simply%20because%20the%20political%20will%20to%20help%20make%20it%20a%20law%20has%20been%20lacking%20in%20the%20lower%20house.%20The%20UPA%20II%20government%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20having%20262%20seats%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20too%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20make%20it%20happen%2C%20citing%20the%20same%20excuse%20of%20being%20in%20a%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGrounds%20for%20opposition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20its%20coalition%20partners%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20(RJD)%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20three%20most%20vocal%C2%A0opponents%20of%20the%20bill.%20The%20other%20two%20have%20been%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20and%20Samajwadi%20Party%20(SP).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20JD(U)%20leader%20Sharad%20Yadav%20who%20infamously%20used%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cpar-kati%20mahilaen%20(short-haired%20women)%20in%20Parliament%20in%20June%201997%2C%20to%20ask%20how%20would%20short-haired%20or%20urban%20women%20would%20be%20able%20to%20represent%20%E2%80%9Cour%20women%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20women%20from%20rural%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20common%20points%20of%20concern%20for%20the%20parties%20opposing%20it%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.legallyindia.com%2Fblogs%2Fblogger%2Flistings%2Fprs-legislative-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPRS%20Legislative%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20been%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20would%20perpetuate%20the%20unequal%20status%20of%20women%20since%20they%20would%20not%20be%20perceived%20to%20be%20competing%20on%20merit.%E2%80%9D%20Furthermore%20it%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThey%20also%20contend%20that%20this%20policy%20diverts%20attention%20from%20the%20larger%20issues%20of%20electoral%20reform%20such%20as%20criminalisation%20of%20politics%20and%20inner%20party%20democracy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20concern%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9CReservation%20of%20seats%20in%20parliament%20restricts%20choice%20of%20voters%20to%20women%20candidates.%20Therefore%2C%20some%20experts%20have%20suggested%20alternate%20methods%20such%20as%20reservation%20in%20political%20parties%20and%20dual%20member%20constituencies.%E2%80%9D%20Also%2C%20rotation%20of%20reserved%20constituencies%20in%20every%20election%20may%20reduce%20the%20incentive%20for%20an%20MP%20to%20work%20for%20his%20constituency%20as%20he%20may%20be%20ineligible%20to%20seek%20re-election%20from%20that%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20report%20(of%20the%20joint%20committee)%20that%20examined%20the%20Bill%20recommended%20that%20reservation%20be%20provided%20for%20women%20of%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20once%20the%20constitution%20was%20amended%20to%20allow%20for%20reservation%20for%20OBCs.%20It%20also%20recommended%20that%20reservation%20be%20extended%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20the%20legislative%20councils.%20Neither%20of%20these%20recommendations%20has%20been%20incorporated%20in%20the%20Bill.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20women%20activists%20backing%C2%A0the%20bill%20have%20gone%20on%20record%20saying%20patriarchal%20thinking%20has%20actually%20been%20behind%20the%20opposition%20to%20it.%20Well-known%20activist%2C%20Aruna%20Roy%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fopinion%2Fpass-the-womens-reservation-bill%2Farticle8324278.ece%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%20Business%20Line%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20March%20this%20year%2C%20also%20argued%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20ranks%20well%20below%20the%20global%20average%20in%20terms%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20representation%20in%20parliament%2C%20as%20well%20as%20amongst%20countries%20which%20have%20mandated%20the%20minimum%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20through%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPoor%20participation%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%20has%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20the%20priorities%20and%20assumptions%20of%20policies%20and%20legislations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CPolitical%20parties%20will%20have%20to%2C%20or%20will%20soon%20be%20forced%20to%2C%20recognise%20that%20if%20parliament%20does%20not%20reflect%20contemporary%20trends%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20education%20and%20excellence%20in%20varied%20fields%2C%20they%20will%20face%20a%20crisis%20of%20credibility.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShifting%20allegiances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20earlier%20stance%20of%20JD%20(U)%20on%20the%20bill%20seems%20to%20have%20changed%20now.%20Attending%20an%20event%20to%20mark%2020%20years%20of%20the%20bill%20by%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%20(NPIW)%20in%20New%20Delhi%20on%C2%A0September%2012%2C%20JD(U)%20general%20secretary%20K.%20C.%20Tyagi%20pledged%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20support%20to%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20come%20to%20say%20that%20from%20today%20onwards%20you%20can%20remove%20the%20name%20of%20JD(U)%20as%20one%20of%20the%20parties%20opposed%20to%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20bill%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tyagi%20said%20at%20an%20event.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20also%20said%20a%20quota%20for%20women%20from%20backward%20classes%20should%20be%20given%20within%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20asked%20whether%20a%20%E2%80%98quota%20within%20a%20quota%E2%80%99%C2%A0would%20be%20a%C2%A0pre-condition%20for%20the%20JD(U)%E2%80%99s%20support%20to%20the%20Bill%2C%20Tyagi%20reportedly%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20should%20be%20passed%20without%20ifs%20and%20buts.%20If%20there%20are%20any%20conditions%2C%20then%20people%20will%20get%20an%20excuse%20to%20delay%20it.%20This%20(sub-quota)%20is%20our%20wish%2C%20not%20our%20condition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECertainly%2C%20this%20is%20a%20ray%20of%20hope%20for%20a%20bill%20that%20could%20help%20change%20the%20gender%20composition%20of%20parliament%20and%20the%20state%20assemblies.%20Even%20though%20the%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20saw%20the%20highest%20ever%20presence%20of%20women%20in%20parliament%2C%20it%20still%20stands%20at%2061%20(11.23%25)%20among%20543%20seats.%20After%C2%A0the%202009%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20there%20were%20only%2059%20women%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESupport%20from%20staunch%20opponents%20aside%2C%20finally%2C%20what%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20bill%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20not%20their%20political%20will%2C%20but%20the%20attitude%C2%A0of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%2C%20which%20has%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20in%20the%20house%20anyway%20%E2%80%93%20a%20unique%20position%20none%20of%20the%20earlier%20dispensations%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20happy%20that%20the%20JD%20(U)%20has%20changed%20its%20stance%20on%20the%20bill%2C%20but%20what%20would%20matter%20the%20most%20is%20if%20the%20ruling%20party%20(BJP)%20expresses%20its%20willingness%20on%20the%20issue.%20The%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20is%20clear%2C%20the%20present%20government%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20need%20any%20political%20party%20to%20pass%20the%20bill%20if%20it%20wishes%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Kiran%20Moghe%2C%20national%20general%20secretary%20of%20All%20India%20Democratic%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Alliance%20(AIDWA)%2C%20one%20of%20the%20core%20forces%20behind%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20BJP%20women%20leaders%20like%20Sushma%20Swaraj%E2%80%99s%20continued%20support%20to%20the%20bill%2C%20Moghe%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20top%20women%20leaders%20of%20the%20party%20will%20also%20have%20to%20push%20to%20pass%20it%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Mere%20support%20for%20it%20is%20not%20enough.%20After%20all%2C%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%C2%A0women%20members%20(Uma%20Bharati)%20who%20stalled%20it%20in%20the%20house%20along%20with%20some%20other%20party%20members.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2FRajya-Sabha-passes-Womens-Reservation-Bill%2Farticleshow%2F5663003.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202010%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Arun%20Jaitley%20said%20he%20had%20a%20feeling%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbeing%20a%20party%20to%20history%20in%20the%20making%E2%80%9D%20when%20he%20came%20to%20the%20house%20that%20day.%20Jaitley%20is%20now%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20players%C2%A0in%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20but%20has%20not%20been%20heard%20talking%20about%20making%20that%20%E2%80%9Chistory%E2%80%9D%20complete%20in%20real%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20maintained%20a%20studied%20silence%20on%20the%20matter%20for%20the%20past%20nine%20years%20despite%20repeated%20calls%20by%20Opposition%20parties%20like%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20Left%20for%20its%20immediate%20passage%2C%20there%20is%20finally%20the%20possibility%20that%20his%20government%20has%20decided%20to%20push%20the%20long-pending%20measure%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695061419000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthew