123091800894_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fadvance-tax-receipts-surge-over-20-to-rs-3-55-trillion-shows-data-123091800894_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fadvance-tax-receipts-surge-over-20-to-rs-3-55-trillion-shows-data-123091800894_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%20cleared%20in%20key%20Cabinet%20meet%20chaired%20by%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695061084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-04%2F11%2Ffull%2F1618159701-0779.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-cleared-in-cabinet-meeting-chaired-by-pm-modi-123091801262_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%20a%20third%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Assembly%20seats%20could%20be%20reserved%3B%20proposal%20likely%20for%2015%20years%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-cleared-in-cabinet-meeting-chaired-by-pm-modi-123091801262_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-cleared-in-cabinet-meeting-chaired-by-pm-modi-123091801262_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fwomen-s-reservation-bill-cleared-in-cabinet-meeting-chaired-by-pm-modi-123091801262_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pending%20For%2027%20Years%2C%20Why%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%20Is%20In%20Focus%20Again%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20Cabinet%20has%20cleared%20the%20Women's%20reservation%20bill%2C%20said%20sources.%20The%20development%20comes%20amid%20a%20special%20five-day%20session%20of%20the%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20MPs%20account%20for%20less%20than%2015%20per%20cent%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20strength%20while%20their%20representation%20is%20below%2010%20per%20cent%20in%20many%20state%20assemblies%2C%20data%20shows%20for%20the%20women%20reservation%20bill%20pending%20for%20nearly%2027%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20concrete%20development%20on%20the%20issue%20was%20in%202010%20when%20Rajya%20Sabha%20passed%20the%20bill%20amid%20marshals%20escorting%20out%20some%20MPs%20who%20opposed%20the%20move%20to%20reserve%2033%20per%20cent%20seats%20for%20women%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20but%20the%20bill%20lapsed%20as%20it%20could%20not%20be%20passed%20by%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20have%20always%20supported%20the%20bill%2C%20opposition%20by%20other%20parties%20and%20demands%20from%20some%20for%20quota%20for%20backward%20classes%20within%20the%20women's%20quota%20have%20been%20key%20sticking%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20parties%20on%20Sunday%20made%20a%20strong%20pitch%20for%20bringing%20and%20passing%20the%20women's%20reservation%20bill%20in%20the%20five-day%20Parliament%20session%20beginning%20Monday%2C%20but%20the%20government%20said%20an%20%26quot%3Bappropriate%20decision%20will%20be%20taken%20at%20the%20appropriate%20time%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20present%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%2078%20women%20members%20were%20elected%20which%20account%20for%20less%20than%2015%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20total%20strength%20of%20543.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Rajya%20Sabha%20too%2C%20women's%20representation%20is%20about%2014%20per%20cent%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%20shared%20by%20the%20government%20with%20Parliament%20last%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20state%20assemblies%20have%20less%20than%2010%20per%20cent%20women%20representation%2C%20including%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Assam%2C%20Goa%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Manipur%2C%20Meghalaya%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Sikkim%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Tripura%20and%20Puducherry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBihar%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Uttrakhand%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Delhi%20had%2010-12%20per%20cent%20women%20MLAs%2C%20according%20to%20the%20government%20data%20of%20December%202022.%20Chattisgarh%2C%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Jharkhand%20led%20the%20charts%20with%2014.44%20per%20cent%2C%2013.7%20per%20cent%20and%2012.35%20per%20cent%20women%20MLAs%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%2C%20several%20parties%20including%20the%20BJD%20and%20the%20BRS%20have%20demanded%20reviving%20the%20bill%2C%20while%20Congress%20also%20passed%20a%20resolution%20at%20its%20Hyderabad%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20meeting%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20not%20known%20what%20percentage%20of%20reservation%20can%20be%20proposed%20in%20a%20new%20bill%2C%20the%202008%20Bill%2C%20which%20was%20passed%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%202010%20before%20it%20lapsed%20following%20the%20dissolution%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20proposed%20reserving%20one-third%20of%20all%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20legislative%20assemblies%20in%20each%20state%20for%20women.%20The%20UPA%20was%20in%20power%20when%20the%20last%20attempt%20was%20made%20to%20pass%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20write-up%20available%20on%20PRS%20Legislative%2C%20it%20also%20proposed%20quota-within-quota%20for%20SCs%2C%20STs%20and%20Anglo-Indians%2C%20while%20reserved%20seats%20were%20to%20be%20rotated%20after%20each%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20meant%20that%20after%20a%20cycle%20of%20three%20elections%2C%20all%20constituencies%20would%20have%20been%20reserved%20once.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reservation%20was%20to%20be%20operational%20for%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20failed%20attempt%20of%202008-2010%2C%20the%20issue%20had%20a%20chequered%20history%20as%20a%20similar%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%201996%2C%201998%20and%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20chaired%20by%20Geeta%20Mukherjee%20had%20examined%20the%201996%20Bill%20and%20made%20seven%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20of%20these%20were%20included%20in%20the%202008%20Bill%2C%20including%20the%2015-year%20reservation%20period%20and%20sub-reservation%20for%20Anglo%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20also%20included%20reservation%20in%20cases%20where%20a%20state%20has%20less%20than%20three%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20(or%20less%20than%20three%20seats%20for%20SCs%2FSTs)%3B%20reservation%20for%20the%20Delhi%20assembly%3B%20and%20changing%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20less%20than%20one-third%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cas%20nearly%20as%20may%20be%2C%20one-third%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20recommendations%20were%20not%20incorporated%20in%20the%202008%20Bill%3B%20the%20first%20was%20for%20reserving%20seats%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20Legislative%20Councils%20and%20the%20second%20was%20for%20sub-reservation%20for%20OBC%20women%20after%20the%20Constitution%20extends%20reservation%20to%20OBCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202008%20Bill%20was%20referred%20to%20the%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Law%20and%20Justice%2C%20but%20it%20failed%20to%20reach%20a%20consensus%20in%20its%20final%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20recommended%20that%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9Cbe%20passed%20in%20Parliament%20and%20put%20in%20action%20without%20further%20delay%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20members%20of%20the%20Committee%2C%20Virender%20Bhatia%20and%20Shailendra%20Kumar%20(both%20belonging%20to%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party)%20dissented%20stating%20that%20they%20were%20not%20against%20providing%20reservation%20to%20women%20but%20disagreed%20with%20the%20way%20this%20Bill%20was%20drafted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20recommended%20that%20every%20political%20party%20must%20distribute%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20tickets%20to%20women%2C%20the%20reservation%20should%20not%20exceed%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20seats%20and%20there%20should%20be%20a%20quota%20for%20women%20belonging%20to%20OBCs%20and%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20standing%20committee%20also%20considered%20other%20methods%20of%20increasing%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20suggestion%20was%20to%20ask%20political%20parties%20to%20nominate%20women%20for%20a%20minimum%20percentage%20of%20seats%2C%20but%20the%20committee%20felt%20that%20parties%20could%20bypass%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20law%20by%20nominating%20women%20to%20seats%20where%20there%20were%20prospects%20of%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20recommendation%20was%20to%20create%20dual-member%20constituencies%2C%20with%20women%20filling%20one%20of%20the%20two%20seats%20from%20those%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20believed%20that%20this%20move%20could%20%E2%80%9Cresult%20in%20women%20being%20reduced%20to%20a%20subservient%20status%2C%20which%20will%20defeat%20the%20very%20purpose%20of%20the%20Bill%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20PRS%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20concluded%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20reservations%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20Legislative%20Councils%20needed%20to%20be%20examined%20thoroughly%20as%20the%20upper%20houses%20play%20an%20equally%20important%20role%20under%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20issue%20of%20reservation%20to%20OBC%20women%2C%20the%20Committee%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Call%20other%20issues%20may%20be%20considered%20at%20an%20appropriate%20time%20by%20the%20government%20without%20any%20further%20delay%20at%20the%20present%20time%20in%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202008%20bill%20was%20opposed%20by%20SP%2C%20RJD%20and%20JD(U)%2C%20though%20parties%20have%20publicly%20expressed%20their%20support%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20will%20need%20two-thirds%20support%20in%20each%20House%20of%20Parliament%20for%20the%20bill%20to%20be%20taken%20up%20for%20consideration%20and%20passing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20feel%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20reserve%20seats%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20due%20to%20the%20existing%20system%20of%20elections%20to%20the%20upper%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMembers%20of%20state%20assemblies%20elect%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MPs%20through%20a%20single%20transferable%20vote%2C%20which%20means%20that%20the%20votes%20are%20first%20allocated%20to%20the%20most%20preferred%20candidate%2C%20and%20then%20to%20the%20next%20preferred%20candidate%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20system%20cannot%20accommodate%20the%20principle%20of%20reserving%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20seats%20for%20a%20particular%20group.%20Currently%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20does%20not%20have%20reservations%20for%20SCs%20and%20STs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20any%20system%20that%20provides%20reservation%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%20implies%20that%20the%20Constitution%20must%20be%20amended%20to%20jettison%20the%20Single%20Transferable%20Vote%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695060720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Frtvrrj68_parliament-generic-pti_625x300_23_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpending-for-27-years-parties-renew-push-for-womens-reservation-bill-4398994%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Women%20MPs%20account%20for%20less%20than%2015%20per%20cent%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20strength%20while%20their%20representation%20is%20below%2010%20per%20cent%20in%20many%20state%20assemblies%2C%20data%20shows%20amid%20a%20renewed%20push%20for%20the%20women%20reservation%20bill%20pending%20for%20nearly%2027%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpending-for-27-years-parties-renew-push-for-womens-reservation-bill-4398994%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpending-for-27-years-parties-renew-push-for-womens-reservation-bill-4398994%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpending-for-27-years-parties-renew-push-for-womens-reservation-bill-4398994%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NDTV%20Explainer%3A%20What%20Is%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20Cabinet%20on%20Monday%20approved%20the%20women's%20reservation%20bill%2C%20sources%20said.%20The%20Union%20Cabinet%20met%20this%20evening%20after%20the%20first%20sitting%20of%20the%20five-day%20special%20session%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20several%20BJP%20ministers%20and%20MPs%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20bring%20women%20constituents%20to%20Parliament%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%20BJP%20president%20JP%20Nadda%20met%20many%20of%20them%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20leaders%20have%20demanded%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20women's%20reservation%20bill%2C%20which%20guarantees%20a%2033%20per%20cent%20quota%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%20Congress%20also%20passed%20a%20resolution%20on%20it%20at%20its%20Hyderabad%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20meeting%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAll%20about%20the%20Women's%20Reservation%20Bill%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20women's%20reservation%20bill%20seeks%20to%20reserve%2033%20per%20cent%20quota%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOne-third%20of%20the%20seats%20reserved%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20will%20be%20reserved%20for%20women%20from%20those%20groups.%20These%20reserved%20seats%20may%20be%20allotted%20by%20rotation%20to%20different%20constituencies%20in%20the%20state%20or%20union%20territory.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20last%20concrete%20development%20on%20the%20issue%20was%20in%202010%20whe